definitions.definition: An English surname from the Celtic Parisi tribe of Yorkshire, the name of uncertain origin. Koch proposes derivation from Proto-Celtic *kʷert ( “ make, cause ” ) , from Proto-Indo-European *kʷer- (compare Welsh peri ).
An English habitational surname , a variant of Paris .
A French habitational surname , a variant of Paris .
A Belgian surname , a variant of Parys .
A male given name transferred from the surname .
